Distribution Class

Source: R/classes.R
Distribution.Rd

Distribution Class

Usage

Distribution(
  type = "dcat:Dataset",
  access = "public",
  bureau = "009:38",
  program = "009:000",
  contact = Contact(),
  identifier = Identifier(),
  publisher = Publisher(),
  resources = Resources(),
  modified = numeric(0),
  title = character(0),
  periodicity = character(0),
  dictionary = character(0),
  description = character(0),
  keyword = character(0),
  landingpage = character(0),
  references = character(0),
  temporal = character(0),
  theme = character(0),
  distributions = list()
)

Arguments

type

<chr> Schema type; default is dcat:Distribution

access

<chr> Dataset access level; default is public

bureau

<chr> Dataset bureau code; default is 009:38

program

<chr> Dataset program code; default is 009:000

contact

<S7_class> Dataset contact

identifier

<S7_class> dcat:Dataset url and nrows in dataset

publisher

<S7_class> Dataset publisher

resources

<S7_class> data.frame of available supplemental resource files; default is NA

modified

<dbl> | <Date> Date Dataset was last modified

title

<chr> Dataset title

periodicity

<chr> Dataset update frequency

dictionary

<chr> Hyperlink to Data dictionary

description

<chr> Dataset description

keyword

<chr> Hyperlink to API landing page

landingpage

<chr> Hyperlink to API landing page

references

<chr> Dataset references

temporal

<chr> Date range the Current dataset covers

theme

<chr> Dataset theme

distributions

<S7_class> data.frame of available distributions

Value

<S7_class> Distribution object
